   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## Part 2.1: Noise! (15 points)\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we're going to investigate whether the ranking SVM is easily influenced by noisy features. For example, what if some of the features you have are in error? Or what if you downloaded only a portion of a page to calculate a feature? (so the count of inlinks would be wrong)? \n",
    "\n",
    "In this case, add some noise to the features. What happens to the results? You may choose to add random noise throughout, noise to a single feature, noise to multiple features, etc. The choices are up to you. We aim to see what kind of exploration you conduct and what you conclude."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Answer\n",
    "\n",
    "The noise was added by using the following experiments:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Deleted entire column(s) of features.\n",
    "    This didn't cause any variation in the error. When I deleted about 20 features entirely, the results were too distorted.\n",
    "    \n",
    "2. Added Gaussian Noise to the individual features one by one, two at a time, and to all the features. \n",
    "\n",
    "    The following library was used for the Gaussian Noise: numpy.random.normal(mu,sigma). The mean mu was kept at 0 all the time while the variance was varied from 0 to 1 in steps of 0.1 and the regularization parameter C was kept to minimum of 0.1. A difference in error of about +2% was found in the result close to when sigma was 0.6 and the noise was applied to all the features. The process is deatiled as follows:\n",
    "    - Convert the train file to pandas matrix using pandas library\n",
    "    - Apply numpy.random.normal(mu,sigma) on all/individual features for mu = 0 and sigma = np.sqrt(np.arange(0.0, 1.0, 0.1))\n",
    "    - Write the file to train.txt and rerun the SVM learn script\n",
    "    \n",
    "Hence we found that SVM is quite robust to noise and there is very small change in error even after deletion of some features. There was a small change in error recorded when we introduced Gaussian noise with the SVM trained with low regularization term. "
   ]
  },
